      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De infamia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e112">Habet, hoc proprium antiqui hostis invidia, ut
              quos in pravorum actuum perpetratione, Deo sibi resistente, superare non valet,
              opiniones eorum, falsa ad praesens simulando, dilaceret.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e127">Sicut bonus odor ex virtute est, sic foetor ex
              vitio.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e142">Gravis est iniquitas, quando is, qui perversus
              est, ostendere et alios perversos molitur, ut inde et ipse quasi sanctus appareat,
              quod alios sanctos non esse docuerit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e157">Ne immoderatis laudibus elevemur, plerumque miro
              Redemptoris nostri moderamine, etiam detractionibus lacerari permittitur, ut cum nos
              vox laudantis elevat, lingua detrahentis humiliet.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e165">Augustinus, <title>de Vita communi
              clericorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e173">Quaerentes licentiam male faciendi, quaerunt
              sibi exempla male viventium; et multos infamant, ut socios invenisse
              videantur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e180">Augustinus, <title>de Vita communi
              clericorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e188">Quia, ut ait Apostolus, <!--<i>-->spectaculum
              facti sumus mundo, et angelis et hominibus<!--</i>-->, qui nos amant, quaerunt quid
              laudent in nobis; qui autem nos oderunt, detrahunt nobis. Nos autem in medio
              constituti, adjuvante Domino Deo nostro, et vitam nostram et famam sic custodire
              debemus, ut non erubescant detractoribus laudatores.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e197">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e207" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e199">Augustinus, <title>de Singularite clericorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e207">Pejus est quam moechia, continentiam ducere
              criminosam; et infamem facere sanctimoniam, blasphemiam ingerit religioni.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e212">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e222" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e214">Ambrosius, <title>super Lucam</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e222">Judicia hominum saepe falluntur, ut et injustis
              justitiae gratiam frequenter ascribant, et justum aut odio persequantur, aut mendacio
              decolorent.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-d1e227">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e237" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Rd1e229">Ambrosius, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e36740-Qd1e237">Quid est quod magis publicum sit, quam offensa
              pudoris, et defloratio virginitatis? Nihil profecto, quod magis se prodat, quam
              castitatis dispendium.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
